# Workflow Test Matrix

Read when: adding, changing, or retiring a user-visible workflow or automated job.
Skip when: no workflow behavior changes.

Purpose: map workflows to the commands that prove them. This keeps local-worker packets and cloud review grounded in named evidence.

## Matrix

| Workflow ID | Workflow | Path IDs | Required Command(s) | Evidence Type | Owner |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| WF-VERIFY-01 | Project verify gate | CLI-VERIFY-01 | `[VERIFY_COMMAND]` | automated | worker |

## Rules
- New behavior should add or update a workflow row when it creates a new user path, API path, job, or operational routine.
- Every row should reference Path IDs from `docs/MASTER_TRACEABILITY_TABLE.md`.
- Commands here must be runnable locally by the worker or explicitly marked manual.
- Cloud review can reject DONE packets when the matrix is stale.
